      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Eroded Self</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jarrett Conner letter on Jeffrey Rosen's April 30 article puts little faith in government's ability to provide adequate Internet privacy safeguards0</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Rosen sounds hopeful that the government may be able to provide adequate safeguards. But I have little faith that such attempts would advance the protection of our privacy. It seems probable that instead of receiving misguided and inaccurate catalog deliveries, we might receive misguided and inaccurate arrest warrants.</p>
        <p>Jarrett Conner</p>
        <p>Brighton, Mass.</p>
      </block>
